civilian /sɪˈvɪljən/

(civilians) 

1. N-COUNT In a military situation, a civilian is anyone who is not a member of the armed forces. 平民 

例： The safety of civilians caught up in the fighting must be guaranteed. 卷入战斗中的平民的安全必须得到保障。 

2. ADJ In a military situation, civilian is used to describe people or things that are not military. 平民的; 民用的 

例： ...the country's civilian population. …这个国家的平民人口。 

例： ...civilian casualties. …平民伤亡。

